{"meta":{"updateDate":1755117017725,"pPcc":"SAT#Q","questionId":"34e18ce4","skill_cd":"Q.B.","score_band_range_cd":1,"skill_desc":"Percentages","createDate":1755117017725,"program":"SAT","primary_class_cd_desc":"Problem-Solving and Data Analysis","ibn":"","external_id":"ee20c3bc-a074-467b-a5ec-dafc0c828d64","primary_class_cd":"Q","uId":"da42e772-492a-4180-bca7-bbf5c7bb8ae3","difficulty":"E"},"source":"modern","detail":{"type":"mcq","stem":"<p style=\"text-align: left;\">There are <math alttext=\"350\"><mn>350</mn>\n</math> objects in a box. Of these objects, <math alttext=\"4 percent sign\"><mn>4</mn><mo>%</mo></math> are balls. How many balls are in the box?</p>","keys":["9bb8aa55-c804-4ae7-b28b-6c1add6023a7"],"answerOptions":[{"id":"decc4ad3-c0f2-4eac-9b5e-23ee44da1e26","content":"<p><math alttext=\"4\"><mn>4</mn>\n</math></p>"},{"id":"9bb8aa55-c804-4ae7-b28b-6c1add6023a7","content":"<p><math alttext=\"14\"><mn>14</mn>\n</math></p>"},{"id":"9ffa4cdd-4ef3-4f02-a18d-af42248a558a","content":"<p><math alttext=\"70\"><mn>70</mn>\n</math></p>"},{"id":"0a8891a4-e931-4f70-995a-3b235df80909","content":"<p><math alttext=\"346\"><mn>346</mn>\n</math></p>"}],"rationale":"<p>Choice B is correct. It&rsquo;s given that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"4 percent sign\"><mn>4</mn><mo>%</mo></math> of the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"350\"><mn>350</mn></math> objects in the box are balls. Therefore, the number of balls in the box can be found by calculating <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"4 percent sign\"><mn>4</mn><mo>%</mo></math> of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"350\"><mn>350</mn></math>, which is equal to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"350 left parenthesis StartFraction 4 Over 100 EndFraction right parenthesis\"><mn>350</mn><mfenced><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>100</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math>, or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"14\"><mn>14</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>Choice A is incorrect. This is the percentage of objects in the box that are balls, not the number of balls in the box.</p>\n<p>Choice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.</p>\n<p>Choice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.</p>","externalid":"ee20c3bc-a074-467b-a5ec-dafc0c828d64","correct_answer":["B"]}}